Frequently Asked Questions about Studying at the University of Nicosia
What programs does the University of Nicosia offer? The University of Nicosia offers a wide range of undergraduate and graduate programs across various fields including business, finance, technology, healthcare, law, and humanities. Additionally, the university is renowned for its pioneering programs in blockchain technology.
What is the language of instruction at the University of Nicosia? The primary language of instruction at the University of Nicosia is English. This enables students from diverse linguistic backgrounds to pursue their studies comfortably.
Is financial aid available for international students? Yes, the University of Nicosia offers various scholarships and financial aid options for both domestic and international students. These may include merit-based scholarships, need-based scholarships, and special grants.
Can international students work while studying at the University of Nicosia? International students are permitted to work part-time while studying at the University of Nicosia, provided they meet certain criteria and obtain the necessary permits from the relevant authorities.
